I love this. I still think getting caught up on the self-insert  trope to dismiss the actual concept of pataphysics is a missed opportunity, but I really like what this has to say about the urge to self-insert in the first place and about escapism in general. As always, I enjoyed the thoroughness you bring to the way the Foundation does things - my favorite detail is footnote 7, how exact they are and how the Foundation personnel themselves have to walk on eggshells.

+though

